data.description: [Core] Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.

schema.description: [Core] Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.

Id.title: Contact ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

IsPersonAccount.title: Is Person Account
IsPersonAccount.description: Read only. Indicates whether this account has a record type of Person Account (true) or not (false). Label is Is Person Account.

LastName.title: Last Name
LastName.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Name.description: Concatenation of FirstName, MiddleName, LastName, and Suffix up to 203 characters, including whitespaces.

Phone.title: Business Phone
Phone.description: Phone number for the contact. Label is Business Phone.

Fax.title: Business Fax
Fax.description: The contacts fax number. Label is Business Fax.

MobilePhone.title: Mobile Phone
MobilePhone.description: Contacts mobile phone number. Label is Mobile Phone.

HomePhone.title: Home Phone
HomePhone.description: The contacts home phone number. Label is Home Phone.

AssistantPhone.title: Asst. Phone
AssistantPhone.description: The assistants phone number. Label is Asst. Phone.

Title.title: Title
Title.description: Title of the contact, such as CEO or Vice President.

LeadSource.title: Lead Source
LeadSource.description: The source of the lead that was converted to this contact.

Birthdate.title: Birthdate
Birthdate.description: The contacts birthdate.Filter criteria for report filters, list view filters, and SOQL queries ignore the year portion of the Birthdate field. For example, this SOQL query returns contacts with birthdays later in the year than today:SELECT Name, Birthdate FROM Contact WHERE Birthdate > TODAY

Description.title: Contact Description
Description.description: A description of the contact. Label is Contact Description up to 32 KB.

HasOptedOutOfEmail.title: Email Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfEmail.description: Indicates whether the contact doesnt want to receive email from Salesforce (true) or does (false). Label is Email Opt Out.

HasOptedOutOfFax.title: Fax Opt Out
HasOptedOutOfFax.description: Indicates whether the contact prohibits receiving faxes.

DoNotCall.title: Do Not Call
DoNotCall.description: Indicates that the contact doesnt want to receive calls.

CanAllowPortalSelfReg.title: Allow Customer Portal Self-Registration
CanAllowPortalSelfReg.description: Indicates whether this contact can self-register for your Customer Portal (true) or not (false).

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity
LastActivityDate.description: Value is the most recent of either: Due date of the most recent event logged against the record. Due date of the most recently closed task associated with the record.

EmailBouncedReason.title: Email Bounced Reason
EmailBouncedReason.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the contact bounces, the reason for the bounce.

EmailBouncedDate.title: Email Bounced Date
EmailBouncedDate.description: If bounce management is activated and an email sent to the contact bounces, the date and time of the bounce.

IsEmailBounced.title: Is Email Bounced
IsEmailBounced.description: If bounce management is activated and an email is sent to a contact, indicates whether the email bounced (true) or not (false).

Jigsaw.title: Data.com Key
Jigsaw.description: References the companys ID in Data.com. If an account has a value in this field, it means that the account was imported from Data.com. If the field value is null, the account wasnt imported from Data.com. Maximum size is 20 characters. Available in API version 22.0 and later. Label is Data.com Key. Important The Jigsaw field is exposed in the API to support troubleshooting for import errors and reimporting of corrected data. Do not modify this value.

Pronouns.title: Pronouns
Pronouns.description: The contacts personal pronouns, reflecting their gender identity. Others can use these pronouns to refer to the contact in the third person. The entry is selected from a picklist of available values, which the administrator sets. Maximum 40 characters.

GenderIdentity.title: Gender Identity
GenderIdentity.description: The contacts internal experience of their gender, which may or may not correspond to their designated sex at birth.
